# Deobfuscated Code

Let me work through this step by step.

## The String Decoding Layer

The code uses a common obfuscation pattern: a rotating string array (`a0_0x111f`) with base64-encoded strings, a decoder function (`a0_0x3e56`), and a self-executing shuffler that rotates the array until a checksum matches. Once decoded, all the string lookups resolve to plain property names.

## Fully Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // 2π (full circle in radians)
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // √(1/2)

// Physics configuration
var config = {
  attraction: 4000,        // Repulsive force strength between all node pairs
  frictionCoeff: 0.004,    // Spring friction/stiffness coefficient
  amplification: 0.92,     // Velocity damping factor per frame
  dispersal: 0.0003,       // Centering/gravity force strength
  inertiaCore: 40,         // Max number of active particles
  streamDecay: 0.04,       // Particle velocity decay rate
  theta: 0.06              // Camera smoothing interpolation factor
};

// Nodes (graph vertices)
var nodes = [
  { id: 'hub',      label: 'Nexus',   r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'alpha',    label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'beta',     label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'gamma',    label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'delta',    label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: 'epsilon',  label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Edges (springs connecting nodes)
var edges = [
  { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state (current and target)
var camera       = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle system
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// Core physics simulation step
function simulate() {
  // 1) REPULSIVE FORCES between all node pairs (Coulomb-like)
  for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      var force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);  // inverse-square repulsion
      var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2) SPRING FORCES along edges (Hooke's law)
  for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
    var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
    var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
    var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
    var force = (edges[e].k || config.frictionCoeff) * displacement;
    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3) INTEGRATION: damping, centering gravity, position update
  for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
    // Centering force (pulls toward canvas center 400, 300)
    nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.dispersal;
    nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.dispersal;
    // Velocity damping
    nodes[n].vx *= config.amplification;
    nodes[n].vy *= config.amplification;
    // Position update (Euler integration)
    nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
    nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
  }
}

// Spawn a new decorative particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.inertiaCore) return; // cap at 40 particles
  var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;
  particles.push({
    x: sourceNode.x,
    y: sourceNode.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI) * SQRT1_2
  });
}

// Update and age particles, remove expired ones
function updateParticles() {
  for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    var p = particles[i];
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      particles.splice(i, 1);
      continue;
    }
    // Apply decay to velocity
    p.vx *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);
    p.vy *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);
    // Move particle
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
  }
}

// Smoothly interpolate camera toward target
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x    += (cameraTarget.x    - camera.x)    * config.theta;
  camera.y    += (cameraTarget.y    - camera.y)    * config.theta;
  camera.zoom  += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}

// Main tick function
function tick() {
  simulate();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();  // spawn particle every 3rd frame
  frameCount++;
}

// Run at ~60fps (16ms interval)
setInterval(tick, 16);
```

## What It Does

This is the **physics engine** for a force-directed graph visualization. There is no rendering code here — this only computes positions.

### The Graph
Six labeled nodes (**Nexus** as the central hub, plus **Alpha**, **Beta**, **Gamma**, **Delta**, **Epsilon**) connected by eight spring edges in a hub-and-spoke topology with some cross-links.

### Three Force Model

| Force | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Inverse-square repulsion** (all pairs) | Prevents node overlap — every node pushes every other node away with force `4000 / dist²` |
| **Spring attraction** (connected pairs) | Hooke's law springs with rest lengths (160–220px) and stiffness constants (0.002–0.006) pull connected nodes toward their ideal distance |
| **Centering gravity** | A weak force (`0.0003`) pulls all nodes toward the canvas center (400, 300) to prevent drift |

### Integration
Each frame: accumulate forces → multiply velocity by damping factor (0.92) → Euler-integrate positions.

### Particle System
Decorative particles spawn from random nodes every 3 frames (up to 40 at a time), drift outward with slow decay, and die after 800–2000 frames. These create the ambient "streaming" visual effect.

### Smooth Camera
The camera smoothly interpolates toward a target position/zoom using linear interpolation with factor 0.06 per frame.

## About the Misleading Documentation

The blog post descriptions are **deliberately inaccurate** — likely meant to confuse anyone reading the source:

- **"attraction"** is actually a **repulsive** force (inverse-square pushing nodes apart), not attractive
- **"amplification"** is actually **damping/friction** (0.92 < 1.0, so it decays velocity each frame, it doesn't amplify anything)
- **"frictionCoeff"** is actually the **spring stiffness** constant (Hooke's law `k`)
- **"dispersal"** is actually a **centering/gravity** force pulling nodes *toward* the center, the opposite of dispersal
- **"inertiaCore"** is simply the **max particle count** (40), nothing to do with rotational inertia
